summary.narrativeincludeclinical:
Combined initial and follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 24 Mar 2011 and 25 Mar 2011 inclusive of legal petition (petition no: 11 CIV 1878): On an unspecified date the male consumer (plaintiff) initiated Aredia (disodium pamidronate) and Zometa (zoledronate) for an unspecified indication and duration. His attorney alleged that as a result of taking this mediation, the consumer developed osteonecrosis of the jaw. He was noted to have injuries, disability, pain and suffering, mental anguish and loss of enjoyment of life. The outcome and causality assessment for the events were not reported.
Follow up received on 17 Oct 2011, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The patient's date of birth was updated. The records dated 06 May 2002, stated that the patient developed sinusitis. The records dated 01 Oct 2002, stated that the patient developed bone cancer. The records dated 04 Feb 2005, stated that the patient developed mild bleeding. The records dated 17 May 2007, stated that the patient underwent extraction of teeth # 30. The records dated 06 May 2008, stated that the patient developed 5 x 2 mm exposed bone on her palate adjacent to tooth # 14. The final outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 28 Oct 2011, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The patient's gender was updated to female. The patient's concomitant medications and drug allergies were updated. The records dated 01 May 2002, stated that the patient developed left facial pain and spinal metastases. On 09 Feb 2004, abdominal ultrasound was performed and it revealed hepatic lesion and hemangioma of the liver. The records dated 14 Jun 2004, stated that the patient developed actinic keratosis. The records dated 23 Jun 2004, stated that the patient developed dysuria and hematuria. The records dated 19 Jul 2004, stated that the patient developed arthritis for which she received Tylenol (paracetamol). The patient also developed depression. The records dated 28 Jul 2005, stated that the patient developed weakness and myalgia. The records dated 27 Sep 2004, stated that the patient developed seborrheic keratosis. On 30 Sep 2004, abdomen and pelvis scan was performed and it revealed small hepatic cyst. On 15 Oct 2004, CT scan of the lumbar spine was performed and it revealed levoscoliosis of the lumbar spine and mild degenerative facet joint disease at multiple levels. The records dated 16 Feb 2006, stated that the patient developed chronic cystitis which led to left pyelonephritis. The patient also developed left lower ribcage pain. On 17 Feb 2006, the patient was admitted for abdominal pain. The patient also developed constipation. The records dated 19 Feb 2006, stated that the patient had fall and noted to have nodules in the right and left lobes of the liver. On 24 Feb 2006, the patient was discharged. The records dated 06 Mar 2006, stated that the patient developed osteoporosis. The records dated 09 May 2006, stated that the patient developed small bowel obstruction for which she underwent valvulation surgery twice. The records dated 03 Oct 2007, stated that the patient developed gastroenteritis. In Aug 2009, the patient developed uncontrollable vomiting. The records dated 11 Sep 2009, stated that the patient developed oral candidiasis for which she received flucan (fluconazole). She also developed hypercalcemia. The records dated 20 Sep 2009, stated that the patient developed mild hypovolemia, bone pain, odynophagia and urinary tract infection (UTI). For (UTI) she was treated with Levaquin (levofloxacin). The records dated 25 Mar 2010, stated that the patient developed pathologic fracture of the left acetabulum. The records dated 17 May 2011, stated that the patient developed edema and acute bronchospasm. The records dated 19 May 2011, stated that the patient developed rash on her groins. The records dated 06 Sep 2011, stated that the patient developed chest discomfort, essential hypertension, pain in jaw, leg swelling, cataract, cerumen impaction and pelvic fracture. The records dated 24 Nov 2011, stated that the patient developed gum pain. The final outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 08 Nov 2011, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The records dated 19 Jan 2010, stated that the patient developed severe left hip pain. The records dated 21 Sep 2011, stated that the patient developed multiple left iliac wing and right proximal femur metastases and diffuse osteopenia. The final outcome of the events was not reported.
Please refer case PHEH2011US08195.
Follow up received on 29 Nov 2011 from the consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Records dated 29 Jun 2008 noted that the patient was no longer on Zometa and using Peridex mouth wash. Records dated 01 Jun 2009 noted the patient diagnosed with renal polyp. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow up received on 11 Jan 2012 from the consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Records dated 10 Sep 2009 stated that the patient was diagnosed with cervicalgia. On 25 Dec 2010, the patient complained about painful respiration. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow up received on 26 Jan 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Chest x-ray was carried out on 31 Jan 2011, it showed multiple rib fracture. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow up report received on 02 Feb 2012, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of the medical records: On 25 Sep 2008, MRI of the lumbar spine was performed and it revealed disc bulging at L4-L5 and L3-L4 and foraminal stenosis. On 03 Oct 2008, MRI of the left knee was performed and it revealed joint effusion. The final outcome of the events was not reported.
Combined follow up reports received on 01 Mar 2012 and 02 Mar 2012, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The patient's surgical history included appendectomy and cholecystectomy. The records dated 08 Feb 2007, stated that the patient developed right axillary folliculitis. The final outcome of the event was not reported.
Combined follow up reports received on 07 Mar 2012 and 08 Mar 2012, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The patient had relevant medical history of abdominal pain, irritable bowel syndrome and mild intestinal ileus. The records dated 06 Jul 2009, stated that the patient developed sciatica. The records dated 30 Aug 2010, stated that the patient developed menometrorrhagia. The final outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 16 Apr 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The patient's concomitant medications included Compazine, Fentanyl patch were updated. The patient was hospitalized on 15 Oct 2009 for intractable nausea and vomiting which was completely recovered at the time of discharge. Record dated 16 Oct 2009, stated that the patient underwent radiation therapy and left breast mastectomy. The patient also experienced intermittent light headedness. Record dated 27 Oct 2009, stated that the patient was diagnosed with metabolic acidosis. The outcome of the events nausea and vomiting was recovered, while for the other events the outcome was not reported.
Follow-up received on 24 Apr 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Record dated 06 Sep 2001, stated that the patient developed breast cancer and autoimmune disease. On 08 Oct 2001, the patient underwent pseudophakia in left eye. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 27 Apr 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The family history of the patient included prostate cancer (brother) and colon cancer (nephew). Records dated 15 Oct 2009 stated that the patient had difficulty in walking and lack of coordination. Records dated 27 Oct 2009 stated that, the patient had hypokalemia and insomnia. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 08 May 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Patient's current condition including metastatic breast cancer was updated. Record dated 14 Feb 2012 noted that patient was suffering from degenerative changes within sacroiliac joints. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow up information received on 06 Jul 2012 from a physician via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. On 13 May 2003, the patient started on Aredia 90 mg monthly for bone metastases. On an unspecified date, the patient started on Zometa for bone metastases. On 03 Nov 2005, the treatment with Aredia was stopped due to osteonecrosis of jaw. On an unspecified date, the treatment with Zometa was stopped due to osteonecrosis of jaw. In Jan 2011, the patient had gone through x- ray which revealed osseous metastasis with progression of the disease. Record dated 31 Mar 2012, stated that the patient underwent partial oophorectomy. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 29 Aug 2012 inclusive of medical records. The patient's medical history included small cystocele, left facial swelling and secondary malignant neoplasm adrenal. The patient's family history included emphysema, heart problems and coronary artery disease. Record dated 09 Feb 2004 stated that the patient had nasal septum deviated and hypertrophy of nasal turbinates. Record dated 11 Sep 2005 stated that the patient had right ankle injury and right talus fracture. Record dated 10 Sep 2009 stated that the patient had lung cancer. Record dated 16 Oct 2009 stated that the patient had sinus tachycardia. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 30 Oct 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Patient's medical history included appendicitis, non specific vaginitis, trigonitis, mild urethral stenosis, urethrotomy. No other medical information was provided.
Follow-up received on 08 Nov 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Record dated 25 Mar 2010 stated that patient had diffuse metastatic disease throughout the pelvis. Outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow up received on 07 Dec 2012 from physician via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Record dated 13 May 2002 noted patient underwent cataract surgery. No new medical information was provided.
summary.sendercomment: Medical Assessment; Review of available data reported in this legal case does not allow for proper causality assessments. Treatment dates are unspecified. Bone mets, conmeds and progression of the underlying cancer all may be factors in most of the reported events.
